The interruption will affect all reservoirs which provide water to Soshanguve, Mabopane, Klipkruisfontein and Ga-Rankuwa. JOHANNESBURG The City of Tshwane says it has imposed water supply interruptions in suburbs north of Pretoria in order to replace a stolen spindle on one of their valves.The metro says it has been informed by the Rand Water supply about an urgent need to shut down the utility s bulk water pipeline.The interruption will affect all reservoirs which provide water to Soshanguve, Mabopane, Klipkruisfontein and Ga-Rankuwa.Spokesperson Lindela Mashigo said, Rand Water technicians are on site to ensure that water supply is restored. The City of Tshwane apologises for the inconvenience that may be caused. 